Usage: set_min_transition [-help] <transition_limit> <object_list>
                          [-clock_path] [-data_path] [-fall] [-override] [-rise]

-help                     # Prints out the command usage
<transition_limit>        # Transition limit value
                          # (float, required, min=-1000000, max=1000000)
<object_list>             # List of objects: ports, instance pins, library cell
                          # pins, clocks or current_design (string, required)
-clock_path               # Apply the transition limit constraint to pins in
                          # the clock network of the clocks defined in
                          # object_list (bool, optional)
-data_path                # Apply the transition limit constraint to data path
                          # pins, where the path is launched by the clocks
                          # defined in object_list (bool, optional)
-fall                     # Apply the transition limit constraint to falling
                          # transitions (bool, optional)
-override                 # Overrides transition limit from other sources
                          # namely library/constraints (bool, optional)
-rise                     # Apply the transition limit constraint to rising
                          # transitions (bool, optional)